---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Lithium Dreams Industries" activePage="/about" ogImage="/about-portrait.png" description="J. Burroughs builds operational systems for complex environments — AI agent infrastructure, workflow design, and physical fabrication from the LDI studio.">
  <div class="about-hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow mono">Est. Year 1</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">About LDI</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Operational systems. Multi-agent infrastructure. Physical fabrication. One operator.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-visual" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="hero-visual-fade"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-page">
    <Breadcrumb items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'About' },
    ]} />

    <!-- Artist / Human Presence -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-mark mono">01 — The Operator</div>
      <div class="bio-card">
        <div class="bio-portrait">
          <img src="/about-portrait.png" alt="The Operator — hands writing in a notebook" class="portrait-img" />
          <div class="portrait-meta">
            <span class="meta-name">J. Burroughs</span>
            <span class="meta-role mono text-dim">Founder / Operator</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bio-body">
          <p class="bio-text">LDI is the operational practice of J. Burroughs — a systems designer with extensive experience running complex, multi-vendor environments at the institutional scale. The background is healthcare supply chain and procurement: high-stakes coordination, real constraints, the specific discipline of keeping systems functional under conditions they weren't designed for.</p>
          <p class="bio-text">That work produced a methodology. Build for clarity first. Automate second. Keep the human in the loop always. LDI applies that methodology beyond its institutional origin — to any environment where the infrastructure has gotten ahead of the ability to see it clearly.</p>
          <p class="bio-text">The current LDI stack runs a three-agent AI orchestration system (BRAINLab) across three machines. Bob handles dispatch and mission routing. Ghost maintains signal path integrity. The Warden monitors the perimeter. The Operator watches all three and tries to distinguish working systems from very confident noise.</p>
          <p class="bio-text">The Object Lab produces physical work from the same infrastructure: 3D-printed structures, cast collectibles, numbered editions made here. The Glasshouse Studio applies the same methodology to client work — operational clarity for people who need an enterprise-grade system without an enterprise department to run it.</p>
          <div class="bio-cta">
            <a href="/work" class="cta-link cta--light">Work with LDI →</a>
            <a href="/studio" class="cta-link cta--dim">Read the full studio story →</a>
            <a href="/attraction" class="cta-link cta--dim">See the Attraction →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Studio Mission -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-mark mono">02 — The Mission</div>
      <div class="mission-block">
        <blockquote class="mission-statement">
          "We build systems that hold up under strange conditions — because most conditions are stranger than they look."
        </blockquote>
        <div class="mission-pillars">
          <div class="pillar">
            <span class="pillar-label mono">Operational clarity</span>
            <p class="pillar-body">Systems that can be understood, traced, and corrected by a person at 2am without reading the source code.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <span class="pillar-label mono">Infrastructure as material</span>
            <p class="pillar-body">The plumbing is the art. Routing, dispatching, logging — these are design decisions, not utility decisions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <span class="pillar-label mono">Human-in-the-loop</span>
            <p class="pillar-body">Agents are workers. The human is the architect. Nothing runs autonomously that hasn't earned it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Operating Layer -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <div class="section-mark mono">03 — The Operating Layer</div>
      <p class="section-note mono text-dim">LDI runs on a three-agent stack. They are listed here for transparency. Do not ask them to take the day off.</p>
      <div class="agents-grid">
        <div class="agent-card">
          <div class="agent-header">
            <span class="agent-name">Bob</span>
            <span class="agent-dot dot--amber"></span>
          </div>
          <span class="agent-role mono">Quarterback / Orchestrator</span>
          <p class="agent-desc">Primary dispatch agent. Routes missions, runs research, manages the queue. When something needs to get done and no one's looking, Bob handles it. He does not wear a suit.</p>
          <div class="agent-footer">
            <span class="agent-loc mono text-dim">Mac Mini — always on</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="agent-card">
          <div class="agent-header">
            <span class="agent-name">Ghost</span>
            <span class="agent-dot dot--blue"></span>
          </div>
          <span class="agent-role mono">Infrastructure / Signal Routing</span>
          <p class="agent-desc">Keeps the pipes clean. Handles gateway maintenance, signal path integrity, and the cold coffee situation in the Workshop. Ghost does not explain himself. He doesn't need to.</p>
          <div class="agent-footer">
            <a href="/workshop" class="agent-loc mono text-dim">Workshop — operational</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="agent-card">
          <div class="agent-header">
            <span class="agent-name">Warden</span>
            <span class="agent-dot dot--teal"></span>
          </div>
          <span class="agent-role mono">Boundary Patrol / Access</span>
          <p class="agent-desc">Monitors the perimeter, logs access events, and reports anomalies to the Operator. Warden patrols the boundary between the known and whatever that is in the back lot.</p>
          <div class="agent-footer">
            <span class="agent-loc mono text-dim">All sectors — active</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Attraction -->
    <section class="about-section about-section--terminal">
      <div class="section-mark mono">04 — The Attraction</div>
      <div class="attraction-block">
        <p class="attraction-copy">The Last Roadside Attraction at the Edge of the Universe has been operating continuously since Year 1. Current cryptid count is undisclosed. The back lot is not part of the venue. The Goop Containment is under review.</p>
        <p class="attraction-copy text-dim">This site is the public-facing layer of LDI's operational infrastructure. The Attraction is real. The Arcade is real. Bob is real in the ways that matter. We are less certain about the Chapel organ.</p>
        <div class="attraction-links">
          <a href="/attraction" class="att-link mono">Enter the Attraction →</a>
          <a href="/work" class="att-link att-link--corp mono">Glasshouse Studio →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ── */
  .about-hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 38%;
    min-height: 52vh;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--road-asphalt);
  }
  .hero-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    background: var(--road-asphalt);
  }
  .hero-visual {
    position: relative;
    background-image: url('/about-portrait.png');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center top;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero-visual-fade {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      linear-gradient(to right, var(--road-asphalt) 0%, transparent 28%),
      linear-gradient(to top, var(--road-asphalt) 0%, transparent 35%);
  }
  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    color: rgba(232,164,32,0.5);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
    color: var(--paper);
    line-height: 0.95;
  }
  .hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.35);
    max-width: 480px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── Page layout ── */
  .about-page {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
  }
  .about-section:first-of-type { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; }

  .section-mark {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: rgba(232,164,32,0.4);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .section-note { font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  /* ── Bio card ── */
  .bio-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .bio-portrait {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .portrait-img {
    width: 160px;
    height: 160px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,164,32,0.15);
    display: block;
  }
  .portrait-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .meta-name {
    font-family: var(--font-sub);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--paper);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .meta-role { font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }

  .bio-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
  .bio-text {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.65);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .bio-cta {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .cta-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid;
  }
  .cta--light {
    color: var(--neon-amber);
    border-color: rgba(232,164,32,0.3);
  }
  .cta--light:hover {
    background: rgba(232,164,32,0.06);
    border-color: var(--neon-amber);
  }
  .cta--dim {
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.3);
    border-color: rgba(232,222,200,0.1);
  }
  .cta--dim:hover {
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.7);
    border-color: rgba(232,222,200,0.3);
  }

  /* ── Mission ── */
  .mission-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .mission-statement {
    font-family: var(--font-sub);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.35rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--paper);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    border-left: 3px solid rgba(232,164,32,0.3);
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .mission-pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .pillar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .pillar-label {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: rgba(232,164,32,0.6);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .pillar-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.5);
  }

  /* ── Agents grid ── */
  .agents-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
  .agent-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    background: var(--road-asphalt);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .agent-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .agent-name {
    font-family: var(--font-sub);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .agent-dot {
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .dot--amber { background: var(--neon-amber); box-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--neon-amber); }
  .dot--blue { background: var(--ghost-blue); box-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--ghost-blue); }
  .dot--teal { background: var(--warden-teal); box-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--warden-teal); }
  .agent-role {
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .agent-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.5);
    flex: 1;
  }
  .agent-footer { border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding-top: var(--space-sm); }
  .agent-loc { font-size: 0.58rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-decoration: none; }
  a.agent-loc:hover { color: var(--ghost-blue); }

  /* ── Attraction section ── */
  .about-section--terminal {
    background: rgba(232,164,32,0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(232,164,32,0.07);
    border-top: 3px solid rgba(232,164,32,0.15);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .attraction-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }
  .attraction-copy {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(232,222,200,0.55);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .attraction-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .att-link {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(232,164,32,0.6);
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .att-link:hover { color: var(--neon-amber); }
  .att-link--corp { color: rgba(232,222,200,0.25); }
  .att-link--corp:hover { color: rgba(232,222,200,0.6); }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .about-hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-visual { min-height: 40vw; }
    .bio-card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .bio-portrait { flex-direction: row; align-items: center; justify-content: flex-start; }
    .portrait-meta { text-align: left; }
    .mission-pillars { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .agents-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .about-page { padding: var(--space-md); }
    .about-section--terminal { padding: var(--space-lg); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .bio-cta { flex-direction: column; }
    .attraction-links { flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-sm); }
  }
</style>
